news.title: Bengaluru has 6,000 illegal layouts; Yelahanka tops the list
news.para: Bengaluru North comes second with 900 illegal layouts spread across 1,080 acres, Bengaluru South 778 layouts in 1,907 acres and Anekal has 501 layouts in 643 acres.

news.title: Meerut divisional commissioner seeks fresh details on erring officials in housing scam
news.para: Surendra Singh had sought details on six points and the GDA had started preparing a report, which would eventually be sent to the state government after being vetted by the commissioner.

news.title: Telangana HC stays auction of 11 acres at Puppalaguda
news.para: ​TSIIC has prepared a schedule for the auction of 95 acres, including the 11-acre land parcel located in survey number 301, at Puppalaguda on September 28.

news.title: Tamil Nadu forms special task force for PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries
news.para: ​The state government has constituted a four member special task force (STF) to expedite identification and distribution of land to beneficiaries of the scheme, according to a senior official in the rural development and panchayat raj department.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA empowers chairman-led committee to decide on site allotment
news.para: In its new order, the authority has empowered a committee headed by BDA Chairman SR Vishwanath to decide on providing alternate sites to the allottees, stripping the BDA commissioner of power.

news.title: Bombay HC grants bail for DS Kulkarni's sister-in-law in economic fraud case
news.para: The bench of Justice Revati Mohite-Dere released the operative part of the order stating that the applicant (Purandare) be released on bail on executing a personal release bond of Rs2 lakh and one or more sureties in the like amount.

news.title: KT Rama Rao to head committee on issues related to regularisation of unauthorised layouts
news.para: The sub-committee would look into issues pertaining to unauthorised layouts, regularisation of plots and house sites, gram kantham and any other issue decided by the committee.

news.title: Gurugram: Building rules flouted in 11 colonies, 57 get DTCP notice
news.para: While the owners of 54 properties made changes in structures or carried out additional construction after obtaining occupation certificates (OC), the remaining three have been running commercial activities — like gyms, salons and showrooms — on their residential premises, DTCP officials said on Tuesday.

news.title: Delhi: Hawk eye on large construction sites to dust out winter pollution
news.para: Construction agencies have been given 15 days by environment minister Gopal Rai to adopt the dust guidelines, but the government may also be looking to incorporate suggestions made by a dust management committee into the winter action plan.

news.title: Only six out of 83 Patna smart city projects completed in four years
news.para: Four years since its selection under the Smart Cities Mission (SCM) by the Centre, only 20% funds have been utilised and six out of the 83 projects could be completed under the Patna Smart City Limited (PSCL).

news.title: Karnataka government to study duty cut for all types of properties: R Ashoka
news.para: He reiterated that the government planned to reduce the guidance value (minimum selling price) of properties, adding that a decision would be made by December. He gave the assurances during a debate on the Karnataka Stamp (Amendment) Bill.

news.title: Chennai development body seals unauthorised constructions
news.para: ​Similarly, shops, an association room, a multi-purpose hall, aa gym and paying guest rooms were locked and sealed in multiple floors of an eight-storey building on the Tambaram-Velachery Main Road at Tambaram over construction violations.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Town planning services under one roof
news.para: The chairman, Devang Dani, said that town planning offices are situated at various places in the city and people have to run from one office to another to get their work done.

news.title: Evergrande woes hit Japan's toilet, air-conditioner and paint manufacturers
news.para: Toto lost 6.1 % on Tuesday, extending its fall since Thursday to 14.8%, on the perceived risk of exposure to Evergrande, which investors fear could miss debt payment later this week.

news.title: Gurugram: Sold sector 69 colony plots flouting rules, ex-MLA kin & 29 others face FIR
news.para: In the letter to the police on Monday, the DTCP stated that the 30 offenders must be made co-accused in an earlier FIR lodged against four persons, including the former Gurgaon legislator, for developing an illegal colony, ‘Avenue 69’, on a five-acre land in Sector 69 without mandatory permission from a competent authority.
